        },
        {
          "id": "9c4663f8b0bc_1",
          "href": null,
          "name": "b253",
          "text": "“Our deepest fear is not that we are inadequate. Our deepest fear is that we are powerful beyond measure. It is our light, not our darkness that most frightens us. We ask ourselves, Who am I to be brilliant, gorgeous, talented, fabulous? Actually, who are you not to be? You are a child of God. Your playing small does not serve the world. There is nothing enlightened about shrinking so that other people won’t feel insecure around you. We are all meant to shine, as children do. … It’s not just in some of us; it’s in everyone. And as we let our own light shine, we unconsciously give other people permission to do the same. As we are liberated from our own fear, our presence automatically liberates others.”— Marianne Williamson (1992, p.190–191)",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 732,
              "href": "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Marianne_Williamson",
              "rel": "noopener",
              "start": 713,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            },
            {
              "end": 711,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 0,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "EM",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "PQ"
        },
        {
          "id": "9c4663f8b0bc_2",
          "href": null,
          "name": "d034",
          "text": "Visions of a healthier world can unite communities, cultures, and humanity into collective action. They can inspire us, as we are positively moving towards a thriving, healthy and sustainable future. It is a very different motivation than fearing peak oil, economic collapse, climate change, and resource wars.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "9c4663f8b0bc_3",
          "href": null,
          "name": "70b2",
          "text": "We all contribute to making the world a healthier place for all of humanity and all of life every day, if we choose to do so. Every one of us counts in making the vision of a healthier world a reality. image",
          "metadata": {
            "id": "1*x5wEiTWxNgdibHQxN-iuHg.jpeg",
            "alt": null
          },
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": "INSET_CENTER",
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 207,
              "href": "http://images.all-free-download.com/images/graphicthumb/water_droplets_ripple_hd_picture_3_165559.jpg",
              "rel": "noopener",
              "start": 202,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "IMG"
        },
        {
          "id": "9c4663f8b0bc_4",
          "href": null,
          "name": "aaf5",
          "text": "There are basically three ways to respond to the complexity of interrelated problems and opportunities we — as humanity and as individuals — are currently confronted with.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "9c4663f8b0bc_5",
          "href": null,
          "name": "5967",
          "text": "The first option is the neurotic response: a denial of the fundamental change that is already occurring and a neurotic clinging to a business as usual that is no longer an option (‘Just keep shopping!’).",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 41,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 24,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "STRONG",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "ULI"
        },
        {
          "id": "9c4663f8b0bc_6",
          "href": null,
          "name": "835c",
          "text": "The second option is a psychotic response: it acknowledges that times are changing and sees aggressive ways of gaining power over resources and people as a way to reduce the negative effects of those changes (‘If you are not with us, you are against us’).",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 41,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 23,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "STRONG",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "ULI"
        },
        {
          "id": "9c4663f8b0bc_7",
          "href": null,
          "name": "f2ce",
          "text": "The third option is a transformative response: understanding change as a healthy process of transformation to a different way of seeing and being — actively envisioning, designing and creating healthier and more appropriate systems.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 45,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 22,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "STRONG",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "ULI"
        },
        {
          "id": "9c4663f8b0bc_8",
          "href": null,
          "name": "e704",
          "text": "Ready for Anything: Designing Resilience for a Transforming World describes Hodgson’s World System Model that provides a deceptively simple way to frame our decisions in the context of everything that is going on in the world. image",
          "metadata": {
            "id": "1*_xPmu9TWIu6AwVBkTJC_cg.jpeg",
            "alt": null
          },
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
