          "name": "2f00",
          "text": "[This article is an excerpt from the Worldview Dimension of Gaia Education´s online programme in Design for Sustainability.] In this section we will take a look at some examples of visions of a healthier world formulated by others: Ted Trainer describes a vision of a conserver society rather than as consumer society. Donella Meadow describes what a sustainable society might look like, based on her 30 years of studying complex living systems in the context of sustainability. John Greco Jr. offers a very personal vision, sharing what his own experience has made him believe a sustainable future might hold.",
