              "href": "https://www.gaiaeducation.org/index.php/en/online",
              "rel": "nofollow noopener nofollow noopener noopener nofollow noopener nofollow noopener noopener nofollow noopener noopener noopener nofollow noopener nofollow noopener",
              "start": 97,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "9c4663f8b0bc_22",
          "href": null,
          "name": "a2e6",
          "text": "The UN Universal Declaration of Human Rights is a vision of a healthier world, and so is the Earth Charter. We will end this module on Worldview with a look at Ralph Metzners comparison of the industrial age that we are moving out of and the ecological age that we are moving into, and a reminder that Design for Sustainability is not about denying the value of any perspective but to transcend and include perspectives that no longer serve.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 44,
              "href": "http://www.un.org/en/documents/udhr/",
              "rel": "",
              "start": 4,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            },
            {
              "end": 106,
              "href": "http://www.earthcharterinaction.org/content/pages/Read-the-Charter.html",
              "rel": "",
              "start": 93,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "9c4663f8b0bc_23",
          "href": null,
          "name": "465e",
          "text": "The conserver society",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 21,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 0,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "STRONG",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "H4"
        },
        {
          "id": "9c4663f8b0bc_24",
          "href": null,
          "name": "3a49",
          "text": "The Australian sociologist Ted Trainer has suggested that we need to shift from a society of consumers to a society of conservers. In his opinion, a sustainable society would distinguish itself through much greater self-reliance at the community and regional scale; people would live more simply, but have a higher quality of life; they would cooperate to create more equitable and participatory communities, and they would need to create a new economic system.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 38,
              "href": "http://www.permaculturevisions.com/TedTrainerssite.html",
              "rel": "",
              "start": 27,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "9c4663f8b0bc_25",
          "href": null,
          "name": "14e9",
          "text": "Ted Trainer. image",
          "metadata": {
            "id": "1*EkNL-wtsUICLYx9ovsyTug.jpeg",
            "alt": null
          },
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": "OUTSET_LEFT",
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 11,
              "href": "http://www.permaculturevisions.com/TedTrainerssite.html",
              "rel": "",
              "start": 0,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            },
            {
              "end": 18,
              "href": "http://www.permacultureaustralia.org.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/Dr-Ted-Trainer.jpeg",
              "rel": "",
              "start": 13,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "IMG"
        },
        {
          "id": "9c4663f8b0bc_26",
          "href": null,
          "name": "502b",
          "text": "He also recognizes that for this shift to occur, a fundamental reorientation and change of value system is needed (Trainer, 1995, pp.9–15). To illustrate his vision, Trainer compiled an instructive list of design characteristics that would guide the creation and re-design of settlements in such a conserver society.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "9c4663f8b0bc_27",
          "href": null,
          "name": "61f3",
          "text": "image",
          "metadata": {
            "id": "1*jVociZl1vTrlkt6hbAJTmQ.jpeg",
            "alt": null
          },
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": "OUTSET_LEFT",
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 5,
              "href": "http://ecx.images-amazon.com/images/I/31fm0VJ780L._SX258_BO1,204,203,200_.jpg",
              "rel": "",
              "start": 0,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "IMG"
        },
        {
          "id": "9c4663f8b0bc_28",
          "href": null,
          "name": "2133",
          "text": "A Vision of the ‘Conserver Society’\n (After Trainer, 1995, p.73)",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 35,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 0,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "STRONG",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "9c4663f8b0bc_29",
          "href": null,
          "name": "844a",
          "text": "Many small villages, throughout cities too.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "ULI"
        },
        {
          "id": "9c4663f8b0bc_30",
          "href": null,
          "name": "84fe",
          "text": "Highly self-sufficient communities; most things are produced locally.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "ULI"
        },
        {
          "id": "9c4663f8b0bc_31",
          "href": null,
          "name": "7efe",
          "text": "Decentralized; many small firms throughout suburbs.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "ULI"
        },
        {
          "id": "9c4663f8b0bc_32",
          "href": null,
          "name": "859b",
          "text": "Few imports. Local sources of most food, goods, energy.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "ULI"
        },
        {
          "id": "9c4663f8b0bc_33",
          "href": null,
          "name": "13c0",
          "text": "Recycle nutrients to local soil.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "ULI"
        },
        {
          "id": "9c4663f8b0bc_34",
          "href": null,
          "name": "4531",
          "text": "Far less need for the car. Therefore dig up many roads.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "ULI"
        },
        {
          "id": "9c4663f8b0bc_35",
          "href": null,
          "name": "4d4c",
          "text": "Most functions carried out by voluntary elected boards, e.g. committee for energy, helping to care for older people, the library, the community woodlots.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "ULI"
        },
        {
          "id": "9c4663f8b0bc_36",
          "href": null,
          "name": "c3b7",
          "text": "Therefore much less need for councils, governments or professional services.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "ULI"
        },
        {
          "id": "9c4663f8b0bc_37",
          "href": null,
          "name": "b058",
          "text": "Many voluntary rosters, working groups and committees.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "ULI"
        },
        {
          "id": "9c4663f8b0bc_38",
          "href": null,
          "name": "20d5",
          "text": "Many co-ops to provide services, e.g. child-minding, mostly non-profit.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "ULI"
        },
        {
          "id": "9c4663f8b0bc_39",
          "href": null,
          "name": "3826",
          "text": "A town bank with an electoral board, so our savings can fund desirable developments in the town.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "ULI"
        },
        {
          "id": "9c4663f8b0bc_40",
          "href": null,
          "name": "e120",
          "text": "Local taxes, providing funds for community development.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "ULI"
        },
        {
          "id": "9c4663f8b0bc_41",
          "href": null,
          "name": "4abf",
          "text": "Plant ‘edible landscape’ everywhere; in parks, parking lots, beside railways, providing free public food.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "ULI"
        },
        {
          "id": "9c4663f8b0bc_42",
          "href": null,
          "name": "3821",
          "text": "Much property owned by the community. Housing, gardens, farms, shops, managed by voluntary elected boards. The residents can set up those enterprises that would enrich the town.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "ULI"
        },
        {
          "id": "9c4663f8b0bc_43",
          "href": null,
          "name": "762e",
          "text": "Most production from local craft, hobby and small firms; few factories.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "ULI"
        },
        {
          "id": "9c4663f8b0bc_44",
          "href": null,
          "name": "7bf5",
          "text": "Residents support (buy from) local suppliers, even though the price could be higher.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "ULI"
        },
        {
          "id": "9c4663f8b0bc_45",
          "href": null,
          "name": "67c8",
          "text": "No unemployment; much part-time work; most people need only low cash incomes. A local work coordination committee shares work among those who need it.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "ULI"
        },
        {
          "id": "9c4663f8b0bc_46",
          "href": null,
          "name": "7704",
          "text": "Town meetings to make important decisions, especially regarding the development and functioning of the town. Participatory democracy.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "ULI"
        },
        {
          "id": "9c4663f8b0bc_47",
          "href": null,
          "name": "22fd",
          "text": "A leisure-rich environment.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "ULI"
        },
        {
          "id": "9c4663f8b0bc_48",
          "href": null,
          "name": "d34a",
          "text": "Public rail and bus services to other settlements and to the city centre.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "ULI"
        },
        {
          "id": "9c4663f8b0bc_49",
          "href": null,
          "name": "5df5",
          "text": "Most people need to work for money only one or two days a week.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "ULI"
        },
        {
          "id": "9c4663f8b0bc_50",
          "href": null,
          "name": "2efc",
          "text": "A few standard models of refrigerators, radios, etc., build to last and to be repaired.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "ULI"
        },
        {
          "id": "9c4663f8b0bc_51",
          "href": null,
          "name": "1e7a",
          "text": "Most of the real economy in the non-cash sector, including barter, free goods, home production and gifts.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "ULI"
        },
        {
          "id": "9c4663f8b0bc_52",
          "href": null,
          "name": "b5da",
          "text": "While these visions of ‘conserver society’ is by now 20 years old, many of the elements are still relevant today. The transformation of society and culture is a process that test the patience of those involved in driving that transformation. Visions evolve with the culture that creates them. […]",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "9c4663f8b0bc_53",
          "href": null,
          "name": "84c2",
          "text": "Note: This is an excerpt from the Worldview Dimension of Gaia Education’s online course in Design for Sustainability. In 2012 I was asked to rewrite this dimension as part of a collaboration between Gaia Education and the Open University of Catalunya (UOC) and in 2016 I revised it again into this current version. The next opportunity to join the course is with the start of the Worldview Dimension on May 21st, 2018. You might also enjoy my book ‘Designing Regenerative Cultures’.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
